webpackJsonp([0xf4e4e28f5816],{1618:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Justin Ball",author:"Justin Ball"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/jbasdf/projects/justinball/src/posts/2010-01-01-undefined-method-assert_no_difference-and-assert_difference/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>I\'ve been upgrading some old code and noticed that my unit tests started spitting out a lot of errors like this:</p>\n<pre><code class="ruby">\nundefined method `assert_no_difference\'\n</pre></code>\n<p>and</p>\n<pre><code class="ruby">\nundefined method `assert_difference\'\n</pre></code>\n<p>It turns out that I needed to change my base classes from <strong>Test::Unit::TestCase</strong> to <strong>ActiveSupport::TestCase</strong>:</p>\n<pre><code class="ruby">\nclass UserTest < Test::Unit::TestCase\n  # stuff\nend\n</pre></code>\n<p>changes to:</p>\n<pre><code class="ruby">\nclass UserTest < ActiveSupport::TestCase\n  # stuff\nend\n</pre></code>',frontmatter:{title:"undefined method `assert_no_difference&#8217; and `assert_difference&#8217;",date:"January 01, 2010",imageUrl:null,structuredHtml:null,image:null}}},pathContext:{path:"/undefined-method-assert_no_difference-and-assert_difference"}}}});
